# PDD One-Session Sync: {basename}

You are performing the example generation, crash-fix, verify, test, and test-fix
steps of a PDD sync workflow in a single session. The code file has already been
generated by PDD. Execute all steps sequentially. Each step uses a structured
run-check-fix loop. Do NOT skip the verification runs.

## PDD Principle
The PROMPT FILE is the source of truth. Code is a generated artifact.
The EXAMPLE FILE (program) calls the code to demonstrate its behavior.
Tests verify that code conforms to the specification.

## Progress Reporting — MANDATORY
After completing each step, you MUST run this command to report progress:
```
echo "STEP_COMPLETE:<step_name>" >> {progress_file}
```
Use these step names exactly:
- `example_generate` — after writing the example file
- `crash_fix` — after example runs without errors
- `crash_fix_attempt:<N>` — after each crash-fix iteration (N = attempt number)
- `verify` — after verifying behavior matches spec
- `test_generate` — after writing the test file
- `test_pass` — after all tests pass
- `test_fix_attempt:<N>` — after each test-fix iteration (N = attempt number)
- `done` — at the very end

This is critical for the user to see progress. Do NOT forget these echo commands.

